00:02:29.989 --> 00:02:33.830
you can use a credit card or your fingernail

00:02:33.830 --> 00:02:37.150
just be careful that you settle it in
without damaging the cable

00:02:37.150 --> 00:02:40.580
and there you have it. The microphone is ready for fitting

00:02:42.140 --> 00:02:44.740
Let's look at fitting it to
ourselves

00:02:44.880 --> 00:02:47.540
Thread the cable through your shirt or your garment

00:02:47.550 --> 00:02:53.670
and then clip it into place. Once it is settled into place

00:02:53.670 --> 00:02:57.230
thread the cable out of a place that

00:02:57.230 --> 00:03:01.810
is not visible to the camera and you can
plug it into your recorder

00:03:01.810 --> 00:03:06.260
in this case I'm just using a smartphone.

00:03:06.260 --> 00:03:10.000
There you have it you really for recording. 

00:03:10.000 --> 00:03:12.340
The position of the mic can vary considering

00:03:12.520 --> 00:03:17.089
a number of factors if there's a lot of
noise around you in the room

00:03:17.099 --> 00:03:20.239
you might need to lift the position of
the mic up

00:03:20.239 --> 00:03:24.090
if the person tends to move their head up
and move it down

00:03:24.090 --> 00:03:28.849
you may have to lower the mic just so you can get a more even recording

00:03:28.849 --> 00:03:31.959
and if the talent as a very strong voice

00:03:31.959 --> 00:03:36.290
you might even need to invert the microphone upside down

00:03:36.290 --> 00:03:40.150
to minimize the chances popping all what
they call plosives

00:03:40.150 --> 00:03:43.750
in some cases you might not even be
able to clip

